1 Analysis

1.1 Data Import

library(readr)
library(ggplot2)
data_45 <- read_csv(
  "data1.csv")
#
data_45$Sex <- factor(data_45$Sex)
data_45$Improved <- ifelse(data_45$Improved==TRUE,1,0)


1.2 Logistic Regressions Tables

1.2.1 Improved ~ Sex logistic model.

#Sex Only
imp_sex_log <- glm(Improved ~ Sex, data = data_45, family = "binomial")
summary(imp_sex_log)

1.2.5 Improved ~ Sex + Height + Weight + Height*Weight logistic model.

#Combined + weight height interaction
imp_combi_log <- glm(
  Improved ~ Sex + `Height (cm)`*`Weight (kg)`, 
  data = data_45, family = "binomial")
summary(imp_combi_log)
## 
## Call:
## glm(formula = Improved ~ Sex + `Height (cm)` * `Weight (kg)`, 
##     family = "binomial", data = data_45)

  1. Sex is a significant predictor of Improved (\(\beta\)= 1.0237246,\(p\)=7.5061887^{-6}).

  2. Males show an increase in the Odds of the subject’s symptoms by 191.708297 %.

  3. When looking at Weight , Height , Sex , and the interaction of Weight and Height the below terms are significant. Note: non-significant terms were removed.

  • Weight (\(\beta\)= 0.1106909, \(p\)= 0.2810184)
  • Height (\(\beta\)= 0.0041262, \(p\)= 0.9345096)
  • Sex (\(\beta\)= 1.0705841, \(p\)= 6.2817138^{-4})
  • Weight:Height (\(\beta\)= -3.8696041^{-4}, \(p\)= 0.5204637)
  1. When comparing the two models from last week and the two from this week on AIC, the [Weight only]/[ Height only]/[ Sex only]/[combination] model is the best.


2 Figures

2.1 Improved vs Height

hei_impr_plot <- data_45 |>
  ggplot(aes(x = `Height (cm)`, y = Improved)) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0, height = 0.02) +
  geom_smooth(
    method="glm", se=T, 
              method.args = list(family="binomial"))+ 
  labs(x = "Height", caption = "https://github.com/akhapwoyaco") +
  theme_bw()

hei_impr_plot

ggsave("hei_impr_plot.png",plot = hei_impr_plot, 
       width = 35, height = 20, unit = "cm", dpi = 400)

2.3 Improved vs Height by Sex

hei_impr_sex_plot <- data_45 |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = `Height (cm)`, y = Improved, color = Sex)) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0, height = 0.02) +
  geom_smooth(method="glm", se=T, 
              method.args = list(family=binomial))+ 
  scale_color_discrete(labels = c("Female","Male")) + 
  labs(x = "Height", caption = "https://github.com/akhapwoyaco") +
  theme_bw()
hei_impr_sex_plot

ggsave("hei_impr_sex_plot.png",plot = hei_impr_sex_plot, 
       width = 35, height = 20, unit = "cm", dpi = 400)
